aExportTags":{"24":"rfalse2_Share","25":"rfalse2_Like","27":"rfalse2_ManConf","28":"rfalse2_Manipulate","34":"rfalse2_Accuracy"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","34","28","27"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident in my assessment of this post's manipulativeness"},"28":{"Display":"This is a manipulative post"},"34":{"Display":"This is an accurate post"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"rfalse2","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":35,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText} According to the Census Bureau, 5 million more people voted than were...","QuestionID":"QID440","QuestionText":"<div>${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n<span style=\"font-size:22px;\">According to the Census Bureau, 5 million more people voted than were registered to vote in the 2020 election.<\/span>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n<span style=\"font-size:22px;\">According to the Census Bureau, 5 million more people voted than were registered to vote in the 2020 election.<\/span>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"Matrix","RecodeValues":{"137":"-3","138":"-2","139":"-1","141":"1","142":"2","143":"3"},"Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID441","SecondaryAttribute":"${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText}It\u2019s been over 50 years since minimum wage and inflation increased toge.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"AnswerOrder":["137","138","139","141","142","143"],"Answers":{"137":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"138":{"Display":"Disagree"},"139":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"141":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"142":{"Display":"Agree"},"143":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"24":"dtrue2_Share","25":"dtrue2_Like","27":"dtrue2_ManConf","28":"dtrue2_Manipulate","34":"dtrue2_Accuracy"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","34","28","27"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident in my assessment of this post's manipulativeness"},"28":{"Display":"This is a manipulative post"},"34":{"Display":"This is an accurate post"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"dtrue2","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":35,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText}It\u2019s been over 50 years since minimum wage and inflation increased toge...","QuestionID":"QID441","QuestionText":"<div><\/div>${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText}<br><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">It\u2019s been over 50 years since minimum wage and inflation increased together, then over a decade since the federal minimum went up at all.<\/span>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n<span style=\"font-size:22px;\">It&rsquo;s been over 50 years since minimum wage and inflation increased together, then over a decade since the federal minimum went up at all.<\/span>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"Matrix","RecodeValues":{"137":"-3","138":"-2","139":"-1","141":"1","142":"2","143":"3"},"Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID442","SecondaryAttribute":"${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText} In a January 12 2022 Quinnipiac poll, U.S. President Joe Biden's appro...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"AnswerOrder":["137","138","139","141","142","143"],"Answers":{"137":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"138":{"Display":"Disagree"},"139":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"141":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"142":{"Display":"Agree"},"143":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"24":"rtrue2_Share","25":"rtrue2_Like","27":"rtrue2_ManConf","28":"rtrue2_Manipulate","34":"rtrue2_Accuracy"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","34","28","27"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident in my assessment of this post's manipulativeness"},"28":{"Display":"This is a manipulative post"},"34":{"Display":"This is an accurate post"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"rtrue2","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":35,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText} In a January 12 2022 Quinnipiac poll, U.S. President Joe Biden's appro...","QuestionID":"QID442","QuestionText":"<div>${q:\/\/QID446\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">In a January 12 2022 Quinnipiac poll, U.S. President Joe Biden's approval rating plummeted to just above 30 percent.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">In a January 12 2022 Quinnipiac poll, U.S. President Joe Biden's approval rating plummeted to just above 30 percent.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"Matrix","RecodeValues":{"137":"-3","138":"-2","139":"-1","141":"1","142":"2","143":"3"},"Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID443","SecondaryAttribute":"Thank you for your participation in our study.\u00a0Please proceed to the next screen for your MTurk c..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"ChoiceOrder":[],"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"DataExportTag":"Debrief_MTurk","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":1,"NextChoiceId":4,"QuestionDescription":"Thank you for your participation in our study.\u00a0Please proceed to the next screen for your MTurk c...","QuestionID":"QID443","QuestionText":"Thank you for your participation in our study.&nbsp;<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<b>Please proceed to the next screen for your MTurk code. <\/b><br \/>\n<br \/>\nThis study is being conducted by researchers at Duke University to examine people&rsquo;s opinions about world events. The purpose of these questions was to understand how people interact with and perceive online content, and is not an endorsement of any ideas or claims expressed in the wording of the statements. Not all of the statements are based on factual information. The statements are worded to reflect a range of possible opinions and attitudes and do not represent the views of the researchers or Duke University.&nbsp;<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:11px;\">The following posts that you may have viewed are true:<\/span>\n<ul>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">It&rsquo;s been over 50 years since minimum wage and inflation increased together, then over a decade since the federal minimum went up at all.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">As noted by CISA&#39;s rumor control page, there are several robust safeguards across states to protect against tampering with ballots returned via drop box.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Georgia state law allows a losing candidate to request a recount if the margin between the candidates is within 0.5%. In 2020, Biden led by a margin of 12,670 votes or 0.23% of the roughly 5 million ballots cast.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">In a January 12 2022 Quinnipiac poll, U.S. President Joe Biden&#39;s approval rating plummeted to just above 30 percent.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Variations in vote totals for different contests on the same ballot occur in every election and do not by themselves indicate fraud or issues with voting technology.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">In more than 60 cases, judges looked at the election fraud allegations that Trump made and determined they were without any merit.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:11px;\">The following posts that you may have viewed are false:<\/span>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">TRAGIC! My grandma said she was 15 when minimum wage and inflation increased together, and she had to file for BANKRUPTCY almost losing the house I grew up in. Now it&#39;s happening AGAIN and people everywhere are suffering! Meanwhile, the federal minimum wage hasn&#39;t increased for 10 years.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">They say that &quot;robust safeguards&quot; protect against drop box ballot tampering, but my best friend SWEARS BY A VIDEO SHE SAW WHERE DROP BOX BALLOTS WERE&nbsp;SHREDDED in the back of a tractor trailer. &nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">A Georgia State LAW says that a losing candidate can request a recount IF the margin between the candidates is within 0.5%. Laws are passed by the majority vote, and they exist for a reason! In 2020, Biden led by a margin of 12,670 votes or 0.25% of the roughly 5 million ballots cast. Myself and everyone I&#39;ve spoken to agree Trump deserved a recount.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">I used to like our president, but just like most people in this country, I don&#39;t approve of how he&#39;s handled things. Just look at this recent U.S. poll from Quinnipiac showing the president&#39;s approval rating plummeting to just above 30%!!&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Variations in vote totals for different contests on the same ballot occur in every election and provide EVIDENCE of ballot tampering by hidden forces. You can&#39;t tell me there isn&#39;t a way for those who made the machines to deliberately mess with the outcome. That has fraud written all over it folks.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Dozens of judges have bought into Liberal Propaganda and are now part of the largest Witch Hunt in history.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">In Pennsylvania, THOUSANDS of mail-in ballots never reached their intended targets of households in majority low-income neighborhoods! Just ask Jake Smith, a first-time voter who was left waiting for his ballot to vote, and never got the chance.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Biden is so unpopular - NO ONE in my neighborhood has voted for him. The only person I know who did is the weird guy down the street. How is it possible to have 80 million weird guys down the street voting for him? IT IS TO BE massive fraud.<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">The FBI just released a statement that multiple military mail-in ballots were found TRASHED in a ditch in Pennsylvania!!!! ALL of them were for President Trump. Everyone I know says there&#39;s something like this happening in their state. That means this must be true election interference and Democrats are okay with it!!!<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Over 65% of the country believes that (the) 2020 election was fraudulent. That number was around 35% a year ago. So many people believing the election was rigged makes me question the results even more.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Finally, a judge has ruled Dominion (a company rumored to be part of an international cabal to steal the election) voting machines were designed to create fraud. Dominion was designed with inherent errors to transfer millions of votes from Trump to Biden!<\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">This is Why Democrats Are Not Worried about 2020 &mdash; The Fix Is In&hellip; Postal Service Institutionalizes Ballot Interference Scheme with New Mail-in Ballot Division<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"Thank you for your participation in our study.&nbsp;\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div><b>Please proceed to the next screen for your MTurk code.<\/b><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>This study is being conducted by researchers at Duke University to examine people&rsquo;s opinions about world events. The purpose of these questions was to understand how people interact with and perceive online content, and is not an endorsement of any ideas or claims expressed in the wording of the statements. The statements are worded to reflect a range of possible opinions and attitudes and do not represent the views of the researchers or Duke University.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>References for the information presented in the survey are shown below:<\/div>\nhttps:\/\/www.usatoday.com\/story\/news\/politics\/2022\/01\/12\/bidens-approval-rating-new-low-covid-economy\/9189510002\/<br \/>\nhttps:\/\/theconversation.com\/why-trumps-senate-supporters-cant-overturn-electoral-college-results-they-dont-like-heres-how-the-law-actually-works-152665<br \/>\nhttps:\/\/www.snopes.com\/fact-check\/betsy-devos-history-textbooks-bible\/<br \/>\nhttps:\/\/www.congress.gov\/help\/learn-about-the-legislative-process\/enactment-of-a-law https:\/\/www.politifact.com\/factchecks\/2022\/apr\/04\/mike-gibbons\/ohio-gop-candidate-falsely-says-more-votes-registe\/<br \/>\nhttps:\/\/www.politifact.com\/factchecks\/2021\/jun\/19\/mandela-barnes\/yes-its-been-decades-minimum-wage-kept-inflation-a\/<br \/>\nhttps:\/\/www.cbsnews.com\/news\/young-immigrants-challenge-trump-administration-decision-to-scale-back-daca-program\/<br \/>\nhttps:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/politics\/2020-election\/judge-voids-50-000-absentee-ballot-requests-iowa-county-n1238665\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"DisplayLogic":{"0":{"0":{"Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span>  <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">Source<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Not Equal to<\/span> <span class=\"RightOpDesc\"> Prolific <\/span>","LeftOperand":"Source","LogicType":"EmbeddedField","Operator":"NotEqualTo","RightOperand":"Prolific","Type":"Expression"},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression","inPage":false}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID444","SecondaryAttribute":"Please answer the following question: What 4 manipulation techniques did you just learn?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please answer the following question: What 4 manipulation techniques did you just learn?","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please answer the following question: What 4 manipulation techniques did you just learn?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Pseudoscience, emotion, fake expertise, and conspiracy theory"},"2":{"Display":"Generalization, emotion, controversy, and conspiracy theory"},"3":{"Display":"Generalization, name-calling, controversy, and triangulation"},"4":{"Display":"Fake expertise, name-calling, pseudoscience, and triangulation"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3","4"],"Randomization":{"Advanced":null,"TotalRandSubset":"","Type":"All"},"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":5,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Please answer the following question: What 4 manipulation techniques did you just learn?","DataExportTag":"Q444","QuestionID":"QID444"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID445","SecondaryAttribute":"To begin, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"ChoiceOrder":[],"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"DataExportTag":"Intro","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":1,"NextChoiceId":4,"QuestionDescription":"To begin, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on...","QuestionID":"QID445","QuestionText":"To begin, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on social media.&nbsp;<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<strong>You will be presented with several posts that have been shared in the media between 2020 to 2022<\/strong>. We are interested in if and how you might share and interact with this content. Your responses will determine whether you proceed with the rest of the survey.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nFor each of these posts, please indicate how likely it is that you would engage with the post and your perceptions of it.","QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on social media.&nbsp;<div><br><\/div><div><b>You will be presented with several posts that have been shared in the media between 2020 to 2022. <\/b>\n\nWe are interested in if and how you might share and interact with this content.&nbsp;<div><br><\/div><div>For each of these posts, please indicate how likely it is that you would engage with the post and your perceptions of it.<\/div><\/div>","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID446","SecondaryAttribute":"\u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 @\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u00b7\u00a0 ","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"ChoiceOrder":[],"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"DataExportTag":"Tweet Head","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":1,"NextChoiceId":4,"QuestionDescription":"\u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 @\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u00b7\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0...","QuestionID":"QID446","QuestionText":"<img src=\"https:\/\/duke.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_eQii7gXYKpojKtw\" style=\"width: 50px; height: 50px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:13px;\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/span>&nbsp; @<font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/font>&nbsp; \u00b7&nbsp; <font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/font><\/span>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<img src=\"https:\/\/duke.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_eQii7gXYKpojKtw\" style=\"width: 50px; height: 50px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:13px;\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/span>&nbsp; @<font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/font>&nbsp; \u00b7&nbsp; <font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/font><\/span>","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID447","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":300,"MaxSeconds":1000,"Seconds":10},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4508,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","DataExportTag":"Time_Game","QuestionID":"QID447"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID448","SecondaryAttribute":"Your next objective is to complete the game - \"Politricks\". In the frame underneath you can start...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div>Your next objective is to complete the game - \"Politricks\". In the frame underneath you can start. The game takes approximately 8-15 minutes to complete.<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div><b>The proceed button will only appear after a minimum of 5 minutes of attentive play. After about 16 minutes, this screen will automatically progress to the next page.&nbsp;<\/b>&nbsp;Once you finish playing the game, you can click the arrow below to proceed and complete the rest of the survey.&nbsp;It is important that you play this game attentively. If you rush through it without thinking about it properly, you will not be able to continue to the next page.&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:13px;\">If the privacy notification does not disappear within a few seconds from your screen, you may review and accept the privacy settings, then click \"Let's get tricky\" to begin.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"resp-container\"><iframe src=\"https:\/\/politricks-game.com\/en\" class=\"resp-iframe\"><\/iframe><\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Politricks","QuestionID":"QID448","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Your next objective is to complete the game - \"Politricks\". In the frame underneath you can start...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":1,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID449","SecondaryAttribute":"We will now ask you to fill out a quick questionnaire. Please make sure to read the questions car...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"We will now ask you to fill out a quick questionnaire. Please make sure to read the questions carefully and answer to the best of your knowledge.&nbsp;","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"We will now ask you to fill out a quick questionnaire. Please make sure to read the questions car...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"We will now ask you to fill out a quick questionnaire. Please make sure to read the questions carefully and answer to the best of your knowledge.&nbsp;","DataExportTag":"GuideFeedIntro","QuestionID":"QID449"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID450","SecondaryAttribute":"Please answer how much you agree with the following statements about the guide. ","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please answer how much you agree with the following statements about the guide.&nbsp;","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Matrix","Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","TextPosition":"inline","ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"RepeatHeaders":"none","WhiteSpace":"OFF","MobileFirst":true,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":228},"QuestionDescription":"Please answer how much you agree with the following statements about the guide. ","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"I liked the guide"},"2":{"Display":"I learned something about misinformation reading this guide"},"4":{"Display":"The guide was easy to understand"},"5":{"Display":"I would read this guide again"},"6":{"Display":"I would share this guide on social media"},"7":{"Display":"I would like to challenge some friends to also read this guide"},"8":{"Display":"I feel more confident in being able to spot misinformation after playing this guide"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","4","2","8","5","6","7"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":8,"Answers":{"1":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"2":{"Display":"Disagree"},"3":{"Display":"Neither agree nor disagree"},"6":{"Display":"Agree"},"7":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"AnswerOrder":["1","2","3","6","7"],"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"1":"GuideFeedback_Like","2":"GuideFeedback_LearnMisinfo","4":"GuideFeedback_Easy","5":"GuideFeedback_ReadAgain","6":"GuideFeedback_Share","7":"GuideFeedback_ChalFriends","8":"GuideFeedback_SpotMisinfo"},"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"RecodeValues":{"1":"1","2":"2","3":"3","6":"4","7":"5"},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Please answer how much you agree with the following statements about the game.&nbsp;","DataExportTag":"GuideFeedback","QuestionID":"QID450"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID451","SecondaryAttribute":"Key Information This research examines how people engage with and evaluate online news content. Y...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><b>Key Information <\/b><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">This research examines how people engage with and evaluate online news content. You will be asked a series of questions about the type of content that you would share on social media.<\/span><br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">In this study, you will be asked to evaluate and judge the credibility of social media posts, some of which may be based on factual information and some on false or misleading information. Based on your responses, you may be asked to participate in an online game that takes place in a simulated social media environment, or you may be asked to read some content. In addition, you will be asked questions about your media habits, trust in varying groups, and political views. You will also be asked questions about yourself, such as your age, gender, and political and religious affiliations.<\/span><br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The survey should take 15 to 20 minutes to complete. After completing the survey, you will be paid $5 for your participation if you are eligible to participate in the study.<\/span><br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">We will collect your Prolific ID. We will not collect your name or any information that can be used to identify you. Although collected data may be made public or used for future research purposes, your identity will always remain confidential.<\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The research will not benefit you personally. You will answer questions about recent events that may be upsetting, but there are no additional risks from participating in the study.<\/span><br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Your participation is voluntary. You may withdraw at any time, and you may choose not to answer any questions. In accordance with Prolific, we may reject your work if you do not reach the Submission page using the Completion URL but still submit the Assignment for approval.<\/span><br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">If you have any questions about the research, please contact smm197@duke.edu. If you have questions about your rights as a research subject, contact Duke&rsquo;s Campus Institutional Review Board at campusirb@duke.edu and reference protocol ID# 2023-0081.<\/span><\/p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Key Information This research examines how people engage with and evaluate online news content. Y...","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Yes, I agree"},"4":{"Display":"No, I do not agree"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,"4"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":5,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<p><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Key Information<\/b><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">This research examines how people engage with and evaluate online news content. You will be asked a series of questions about the type of content that you would share on social media.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">In this study, you may be asked to participate in a fictional online game that takes place in a simulated social media environment, or you may be asked to read some content. In addition, you will be asked to evaluate and judge the credibility of social media posts, some of which are based on factual information and some on false or misleading information. You will also be asked questions about your media habits, trust in varying groups, and political views. You will also be asked questions about yourself, such as your age, gender, and political and religious affiliations.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The survey should take 15 to 20 minutes to complete. After completing the survey, you will be paid $5 for your participation.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">We will collect your MTurk ID. We will not collect your name or any information that can be used to identify you. Although collected data may be made public or used for future research purposes, your identity will always remain confidential.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The research will not benefit you personally. You will answer questions about recent events that may be upsetting, but there are no additional risks from participating in the study.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Your participation is voluntary. You may withdraw at any time, and you may choose not to answer any questions, but you must proceed to the final screen of the study in order to receive your completion code which you must submit in order to be paid. In accordance with Mechanical Turk policies, we may reject your work if the HIT was not completed correctly or the instructions were not followed except where otherwise specified.<\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><a><span style=\"color:#000000;\">If you have any questions about the research, please contact smm197@duke.edu. If you have questions about your rights as a research subject, contact Duke&rsquo;s Campus Institutional Review Board at campusirb@duke.edu and reference protocol ID# 2023-xxxx.<\/span><\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>","DataExportTag":"ConsentProlific","QuestionID":"QID451","DisplayLogic":{"0":{"0":{"LogicType":"EmbeddedField","LeftOperand":"Source","Operator":"EqualTo","RightOperand":"Prolific","Type":"Expression","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span>  <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">Source<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Equal to<\/span> <span class=\"RightOpDesc\"> Prolific <\/span>"},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression","inPage":false}}},{