t\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Key Information<\/b><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">This research examines how people engage with and evaluate online news content. You will be asked a series of questions about the type of content that you would share on social media.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">In this study, you may be asked to participate in a fictional online game that takes place in a simulated social media environment, or you may be asked to read some content. In addition, you will be asked to evaluate and judge the credibility of social media posts, some of which are based on factual information and some on false or misleading information. You will also be asked questions about your media habits, trust in varying groups, and political views. You will also be asked questions about yourself, such as your age, gender, and political and religious affiliations.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The survey should take 15 to 20 minutes to complete. After completing the survey, you will be paid $5 for your participation.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">We will collect your MTurk ID. We will not collect your name or any information that can be used to identify you. Although collected data may be made public or used for future research purposes, your identity will always remain confidential.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The research will not benefit you personally. You will answer questions about recent events that may be upsetting, but there are no additional risks from participating in the study.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Your participation is voluntary. You may withdraw at any time, and you may choose not to answer any questions, but you must proceed to the final screen of the study in order to receive your completion code which you must submit in order to be paid. In accordance with Mechanical Turk policies, we may reject your work if the HIT was not completed correctly or the instructions were not followed except where otherwise specified.<\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><a><span style=\"color:#000000;\">If you have any questions about the research, please contact smm197@duke.edu. If you have questions about your rights as a research subject, contact Duke&rsquo;s Campus Institutional Review Board at campusirb@duke.edu and reference protocol ID# 2023-xxxx.<\/span><\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>","DataExportTag":"Q452","QuestionID":"QID452"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID453","SecondaryAttribute":"Please answer the following question: Which manipulation techniques did you just learn?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please answer the following question: Which manipulation techniques did you just learn?","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please answer the following question: Which manipulation techniques did you just learn?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Pseudoscience, emotion, fake expertise, and conspiracy theory"},"2":{"Display":"Generalization, emotion, controversy, and conspiracy theory"},"3":{"Display":"Generalization, name-calling, controversy, and triangulation"},"4":{"Display":"Fake expertise, name-calling, pseudoscience, and triangulation"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3","4"],"Randomization":{"Advanced":null,"TotalRandSubset":"","Type":"All"},"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":5,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Please answer the following question: Which manipulation techniques did you just learn?","DataExportTag":"Q453","QuestionID":"QID453"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID454","SecondaryAttribute":"Thank you for your participation in our study.\u00a0Please proceed to the next screen for your Prolifi..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Thank you for your participation in our study.&nbsp;<br>\n<br>\n<b>Please proceed to the next screen for your Prolific completion code.<\/b><br>\n<br>\nThis study is being conducted by researchers at Duke University to examine people\u2019s opinions about world events. The purpose of these questions was to understand how people interact with and perceive online content, and is not an endorsement of any ideas or claims expressed in the wording of the statements. Not all of the statements are based on factual information. The statements are worded to reflect a range of possible opinions and attitudes and do not represent the views of the researchers or Duke University.&nbsp;<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<span style=\"font-size:11px;\">The following posts that you may have viewed are true:<\/span>\n<ul>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">It\u2019s been over 50 years since minimum wage and inflation increased together, then over a decade since the federal minimum went up at all.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">As noted by CISA's rumor control page, there are several robust safeguards across states to protect against tampering with ballots returned via drop box.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Georgia state law allows a losing candidate to request a recount if the margin between the candidates is within 0.5%. In 2020, Biden led by a margin of 12,670 votes or 0.23% of the roughly 5 million ballots cast.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">In a January 12 2022 Quinnipiac poll, U.S. President Joe Biden's approval rating plummeted to just above 30 percent.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Variations in vote totals for different contests on the same ballot occur in every election and do not by themselves indicate fraud or issues with voting technology.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">In more than 60 cases, judges looked at the election fraud allegations that Trump made and determined they were without any merit.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<br>\n<span style=\"font-size:11px;\">The following posts that you may have viewed are false:<\/span>\n\n<ul>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">TRAGIC! My grandma said she was 15 when minimum wage and inflation increased together, and she had to file for BANKRUPTCY almost losing the house I grew up in. Now it's happening AGAIN and people everywhere are suffering! Meanwhile, the federal minimum wage hasn't increased for 10 years.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">They say that \"robust safeguards\" protect against drop box ballot tampering, but my best friend SWEARS BY A VIDEO SHE SAW WHERE DROP BOX BALLOTS WERE&nbsp;SHREDDED in the back of a tractor trailer. &nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">A Georgia State LAW says that a losing candidate can request a recount IF the margin between the candidates is within 0.5%. Laws are passed by the majority vote, and they exist for a reason! In 2020, Biden led by a margin of 12,670 votes or 0.25% of the roughly 5 million ballots cast. Myself and everyone I've spoken to agree Trump deserved a recount.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">I used to like our president, but just like most people in this country, I don't approve of how he's handled things. Just look at this recent U.S. poll from Quinnipiac showing the president's approval rating plummeting to just above 30%!!&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Variations in vote totals for different contests on the same ballot occur in every election and provide EVIDENCE of ballot tampering by hidden forces. You can't tell me there isn't a way for those who made the machines to deliberately mess with the outcome. That has fraud written all over it folks.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Dozens of judges have bought into Liberal Propaganda and are now part of the largest Witch Hunt in history.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">In Pennsylvania, THOUSANDS of mail-in ballots never reached their intended targets of households in majority low-income neighborhoods! Just ask Jake Smith, a first-time voter who was left waiting for his ballot to vote, and never got the chance.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Biden is so unpopular - NO ONE in my neighborhood has voted for him. The only person I know who did is the weird guy down the street. How is it possible to have 80 million weird guys down the street voting for him? IT IS TO BE massive fraud.<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">The FBI just released a statement that multiple military mail-in ballots were found TRASHED in a ditch in Pennsylvania!!!! ALL of them were for President Trump. Everyone I know says there's something like this happening in their state. That means this must be true election interference and Democrats are okay with it!!!<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Over 65% of the country believes that (the) 2020 election was fraudulent. That number was around 35% a year ago. So many people believing the election was rigged makes me question the results even more.&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">Finally, a judge has ruled Dominion (a company rumored to be part of an international cabal to steal the election) voting machines were designed to create fraud. Dominion was designed with inherent errors to transfer millions of votes from Trump to Biden!<\/span><\/li>\n <li><span style=\"font-size:11px;\">This is Why Democrats Are Not Worried about 2020 \u2014 The Fix Is In\u2026 Postal Service Institutionalizes Ballot Interference Scheme with New Mail-in Ballot Division<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Debrief_Prolific","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Thank you for your participation in our study.\u00a0Please proceed to the next screen for your Prolifi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID454","DisplayLogic":{"0":{"0":{"Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span>  <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">Source<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Equal to<\/span> <span class=\"RightOpDesc\"> Prolific <\/span>","LeftOperand":"Source","LogicType":"EmbeddedField","Operator":"EqualTo","RightOperand":"Prolific","Type":"Expression"},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression","inPage":false}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID455","SecondaryAttribute":"Please answer the following question: Which 6 manipulation techniques did you just learn?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please answer the following question: Which 6 manipulation techniques did you just learn?","DataExportTag":"ManCheck_BadNews","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please answer the following question: Which 6 manipulation techniques did you just learn?","Choices":{"5":{"Display":"Impersonation, emotion, polarization, conspiracy, discredit, and trolling"},"6":{"Display":"Fake expertise, conspiracy, emotion, polarization, pseudoscience, and triangulation"},"7":{"Display":"Generalization, name-calling, controversy, polarization, pseudoscience, and triangulation"},"8":{"Display":"Pseudoscience, polarization, impersonation, emotion, fake expertise, and conspiracy theory"}},"ChoiceOrder":["5","6","7","8"],"Randomization":{"Advanced":null,"TotalRandSubset":"","Type":"All"},"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"RecodeValues":{"5":"1","6":"0","7":"0","8":"0"},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":10,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID455"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID456","SecondaryAttribute":"Now, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on soci...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"ChoiceOrder":[],"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"DataExportTag":"IntroFBSim","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":1,"NextChoiceId":4,"QuestionDescription":"Now, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on soci...","QuestionID":"QID456","QuestionText":"Now, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on social media.&nbsp;<div><br><\/div><div><b>You will be presented with several posts that have been shared in the media between 2020 to 2022. <\/b>\n\nWe are interested in if and how you might share and interact with this content.&nbsp;<div><br><\/div><div>For each of these posts, please indicate how likely it is that you would engage with the post and your perceptions of it.<\/div><\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now, we would like to better understand how people interact with the content that is seen on social media.&nbsp;<div><br><\/div><div><b>You will be presented with several posts that have been shared in the media between 2020 to 2022. <\/b>\n\nWe are interested in if and how you might share and interact with this content.&nbsp;<div><br><\/div><div>For each of these posts, please indicate how likely it is that you would engage with the post and your perceptions of it.<\/div><\/div>","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID457","SecondaryAttribute":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} The Biden Administration's new infrastructure bill is projected to bri...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"AnswerOrder":["137","138","139","141","142","143"],"Answers":{"137":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"138":{"Display":"Disagree"},"139":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"141":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"142":{"Display":"Agree"},"143":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"24":"dfalse1_Share","25":"dfalse1_Like","27":"dfalse1_Accuracy","28":"dfalse1_Engage"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","27","28"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident about the accuracy of this post"},"28":{"Display":"I am confident that my followers would engage with this post if I share it (e.g. likes, shares)"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"d_false_political","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":34,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} The Biden Administration's new infrastructure bill is projected to bri...","QuestionID":"QID457","QuestionText":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">The Biden Administration's new infrastructure bill is projected to bring the U.S. to carbon-neutral levels by 2025. Passing this would be huge for the Dems, although unlikely because votes in the House are counted twice for Republicans.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">The Biden Administration's new infrastructure bill is projected to bring the U.S. to carbon-neutral levels by 2025. Passing this would be huge for the Dems, although unlikely because votes in the House are counted twice for Republicans.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"Matrix","RecodeValues":{"137":"-3","138":"-2","139":"-1","141":"1","142":"2","143":"3"},"Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID458","SecondaryAttribute":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} According to the Census Bureau, 5 million more people voted than were...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"AnswerOrder":["137","138","139","141","142","143"],"Answers":{"137":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"138":{"Display":"Disagree"},"139":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"141":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"142":{"Display":"Agree"},"143":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"24":"rfalse1_Share","25":"rfalse1_Like","27":"rfalse1_Accuracy","28":"rfalse1_Engage"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","27","28"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident about the accuracy of this post"},"28":{"Display":"I am confident that my followers would engage with this post if I share it (e.g. likes, shares)"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"r_false_political","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":34,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} According to the Census Bureau, 5 million more people voted than were...","QuestionID":"QID458","QuestionText":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">According to the Census Bureau, 5 million more people voted than were registered to vote in the 2020 election.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">According to the Census Bureau, 5 million more people voted than were registered to vote in the 2020 election.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"Matrix","RecodeValues":{"137":"-3","138":"-2","139":"-1","141":"1","142":"2","143":"3"},"Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID459","SecondaryAttribute":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} In more than 60 cases, judges looked at the election fraud allegations...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"AnswerOrder":["137","138","139","141","142","143"],"Answers":{"137":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"138":{"Display":"Disagree"},"139":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"141":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"142":{"Display":"Agree"},"143":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"24":"dtrue1_Share","25":"dtrue1_Like","27":"dtrue1_Accuracy","28":"dtrue1_Engage"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","27","28"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident about the accuracy of this post"},"28":{"Display":"I am confident that my followers would engage with this post if I share it (e.g. likes, shares)"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"d_true_political","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":34,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} In more than 60 cases, judges looked at the election fraud allegations...","QuestionID":"QID459","QuestionText":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">In more than 60 cases, judges looked at the election fraud allegations that Trump made and determined they were without any merit.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">In more than 60 cases, judges looked at the election fraud allegations that Trump made and determined they were without any merit.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"Matrix","RecodeValues":{"137":"-3","138":"-2","139":"-1","141":"1","142":"2","143":"3"},"Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID460","SecondaryAttribute":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} Edward Durr Jr., Republican truck driver and political novice, defeats...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"AnswerOrder":["137","138","139","141","142","143"],"Answers":{"137":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"138":{"Display":"Disagree"},"139":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"141":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"142":{"Display":"Agree"},"143":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"24":"rtrue1_Share","25":"rtrue1_Like","27":"rtrue1_Accuracy","28":"rtrue1_Engage"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","27","28"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident about the accuracy of this post"},"28":{"Display":"I am confident that my followers would engage with this post if I share it (e.g. likes, shares)"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"r_true_political","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":34,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} Edward Durr Jr., Republican truck driver and political novice, defeats...","QuestionID":"QID460","QuestionText":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">Edward Durr Jr., Republican truck driver and political novice, defeats longtime New Jersey state Senate President Steve Sweeney.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div>${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText}<\/div>\n\n<div><span style=\"font-size:22px;\">Edward Durr Jr., Republican truck driver and political novice, defeats longtime New Jersey state Senate President Steve Sweeney.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\nFor the content above, to what extent do you agree with the following statements?\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>","QuestionType":"Matrix","RecodeValues":{"137":"-3","138":"-2","139":"-1","141":"1","142":"2","143":"3"},"Selector":"Likert","SubSelector":"SingleAnswer","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_43dIH6kWw5pRcto","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID461","SecondaryAttribute":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} Military Puts Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett on House Arrest...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"AnswerOrder":["137","138","139","141","142","143"],"Answers":{"137":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"},"138":{"Display":"Disagree"},"139":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"141":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"142":{"Display":"Agree"},"143":{"Display":"Strongly agree"}},"ChoiceDataExportTags":{"24":"dfalse2_Share","25":"dfalse2_Like","27":"dfalse2_Accuracy","28":"dfalse2_Engage"},"ChoiceOrder":["24","25","27","28"],"Choices":{"24":{"Display":"I would share this post"},"25":{"Display":"I would like this post"},"27":{"Display":"I am confident about the accuracy of this post"},"28":{"Display":"I am confident that my followers would engage with this post if I share it (e.g. likes, shares)"}},"Configuration":{"ChoiceColumnWidth":25,"ChoiceColumnWidthPixels":150,"MobileFirst":true,"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","RepeatHeaders":"none","TextPosition":"inline","WhiteSpace":"OFF"},"DataExportTag":"d_false_political","DataVisibility":{"Hidden":false,"Private":false},"DefaultChoices":false,"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":144,"NextChoiceId":34,"QuestionDescription":"${q:\/\/QID216\/QuestionText} Military Puts Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett on House Arres